article.headline: San Diego 48, Valparaiso 7
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Sam Scudellari passed for 232 yards and three touchdowns as San Deigo beat Valparaiso 48-7 Saturday afternoon. Scudellari found Eric Fiege on a 41-yard scoring pass in the second. He also connected with Kyle Warren on a 28-yard throw and John McGough on a 20 yarder. Matt Jelmini and JT Rogan rushed for scores of 22 and 14 yards for San Diego (3-2, 2-1). Gabriel Derricks picked off Nate Goergen and scored on the 26-yard return. Joe Martin scored on a 38-yard return after intercepting Bobby Wysocki. Eddie Morelli gave the Crusaders (1-4, 0-2) their only score of the game with a 3-yard run in the third.
